sharedSelectionEntries.name: ODST Special Purpose Trooper (BR55 Battle Rifle)

characteristics.$text:
To represent the extraordinary abilities of the Master Chief, at the start of the Master chief's activation you may use a Special Order result to allow the use of any number of Advance, Assault, or Shoot command dice results during that activation.

The Master Chief may also use the Snap Shot special order.


The Master Chief may be taken in place of 2 other Spartans when drafting your Spartan fireteam.
characteristics.name: Details

characteristics.$text:
At the start of each round, immediately after rolling command dice is completed, you may spend a Special Order result to take one face-down item token from the supply pile and place it in any cube which contains no models.

Do not look at the item when placing it. If the location contains a building, it must be placed on the highest level of the stack.


You may spend any number of Special Order results in this way. Choose a different cube for each item placed.
characteristics.name: Details

characteristics.$text:
You may only use this special order once per round. It does not require Veronica Dare to be present on the board at the time of use.
At the start of the round, immediately after Command dice have been rolled and any rerolls performed, spend a Special Order result to change 2 of your remaining command dice to results of your choice.

profiles.name: Your Orders Have Changed (Must include Dare)

sharedSelectionEntries.name: Your Orders Have Changed (Must include Dare)

characteristics.$text:
When an ODST is respawning: Instead of using its first action to advance onto the board at a respawn point, you may spend a Special Order result to take on auxiliary action instead to deploy the model into any cube on the board which contains no models. If location contains a building, it must be placed on the highest level stack. Roll a 3 dice Ranged test (2). No effect if the test is passed. If failed, the model is Pinned and scatters into an adjacent cube (make a Scatter roll to determine which direction - this is forced movement from the target cube)


At the start of the first round: Immediately after rolling command dice is completed, you may spend a Special Order result to remove one friendly ODST from the board and redeploy it as described above (model placement and the Ranged test). When that model activates, it will only have one short action to use that turn (ignore this restriction if the model is killed before it activates). You may spend any number of Special Order results to redeploy that many ODST.
characteristics.name: Details

characteristics.$text:
When a grenade lands in the same cube as a friendly Spartan, you may spend a Special Order result to allow that Spartan to attempt to catch it and throw it. It doesn't matter if the grenade was thrown accurately or scattered into the cube. May only be used with weapons/items called a ____ Grenade (e.g. Plasma Grenade), not any kind of grenade launcher or other weapon which shoots grenades. You must declare the use of the Special Order before your opponent resolves the effect of the grenade (rolling Frag, etc.)


First, roll a 3 dice Survive test (2) to catch the grenade. If you roll 1 or 0 successes, the catch failed and the grenade is resolved as normal. If you roll the 2 or more successes required, the Spartan may then throw the grenade as if making a Shoot action. You resolve the grenade effects wherever it lands (it is your grenade now).
characteristics.name: Details

characteristics.$text:
When: When one of your opponent's models moves into a cube which contains one of your models using an Advance or Sprint action which woudl trigger a free Assault action. Your opponent must specify which of your models is being attacked, if there is more than one in the cube, before this Special Order use is declared. Before the free ASsault action is performed, declare the use of this Special Order and discard the Command Die showing that result. May not be used if there is already another enemy model in the cube with your model or if your model is Pinned.


What: The model being assaulted may make a free Shoot action against the attacker (short action only). Use one of the model's equipped ranged weapons, including all the keywords for that weapon, but do not apply the following Shoot action modifiers: Clear shot, High Ground, Friendly Fire. Apply damage to the enmy model as normal. If the Shoot attack cuases the enemy model to be moved out of the cube (e.g. Knockback) or Pinned, the opponent's free Assault action does not take place.
